        <p>Representative Michael P. Forbes, the Long Island congressman who switched from the Republican Party to the Democrats last summer, was endorsed yesterday by the Suffolk County Democratic Party.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Representative Michael P. Forbes, the Long Island congressman who switched from the Republican Party to the Democrats last summer, was endorsed yesterday by the Suffolk County Democratic Party.</p>
        <p>The move ended speculation that he would be opposed within his newly adopted party. The Democrats had threatened to run a candidate against him unless he refused re-endorsement by the Right to Life Party. He refused the endorsement.</p>
        <p>METRO NEWS BRIEFS: NEW YORK</p>
      </block>
